The paper deals with game theory and algorithms, which are typically categorized under cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of logit dynamics and Markov chains also suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper's focus on equilibrium concepts and convergence measures may also place it under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
